node.text:
#perspective and how life teaches us some important lessons....
🔸️Last year this time, I was celebrating the end of Melbourne winters in the city 🏙 
It was a CRAZY DAY where everything was going wrong🙄 First I missed my train 🚆 because of the kids and their dinner tantrums..then the train I was on had a technical problem 😒 so hopped on to the replacement bus 🚌 ...that bus had an accident🤦‍♀️..so took another bus..that bus dropped me far from my destination, so ended up walking another 15 minutes in chilly Melbourne weather😩 By the time I reached, I was exhausted, frustrated and more than an hour late!!! 
🔸️
...BUT I hadn't met 2020 then 🤪 so it was still an awesome day...a day I will swap with today in a heartbeat!! I had no idea that one day I will miss the discomfort of a very inconvenient public transport 🙄 because I'm willing to go through it again, if that means this stupid pandemic is over and I get to REALLY live in one of #worldsmostliveablecity , Melbourne 💞
🔸️
So here's a BIG cheers 🥂 to the GOOD days that only get appreciated on a BAD DAY, cheers to the things we take for granted until we don't have them anymore and cheers to the struggles that make us feel grateful for everything we have NOW🙏

Do you feel the wind in your hair and the sand at your feet? 

Once in while when it gets heavy to sit at home and life gets you down, go out. You do not need anyone. 
Just feel the breeze and be with nature. 

A few minutes will transform everything.

On second thoughts, how is Monday?

node.text:
I am not a very big fan of Cheesecakes but I was willing to try Cheesecake. So, this weekend I tried making Oreo Cheesecake. I loved how it turned out. Just be mindful about the portion size. 😁

Here's the recipe for you'll to try! 

Ingredients:
1 packet Oreo biscuits
2 Tbsp Melted Butter
1/2 Cup Heavy Cream
1 Tsp Vanilla Essence
1 Tbsp Icing Sugar
75 gms Cream Cheese
3-4 broken Oreo biscuits for garnishing

Procedure:
Separate the cream from the Oreo biscuits and keep it side.
Grind the biscuits in the mixture. 
Add the Melted Butter in the grinded biscuits  and mix it well. 
Spread the mixture in a Butter greased mould and set it in the fridge for 1 hour. 
Whip the Heavy Cream lightly.
Add Vanilla Essence and Icing Sugar.
Whip the Cream Cheese lightly. 
Combine the whipped Cream and Cream Cheese, Oreo Cream. Whip till completely mixed together.
Remove the mould from the fridge and spread the Cream on the set Oreo base in the mould. 
Garnish it with broken pieces of Oreo biscuits. 
Chill the Oreo Cheesecake atleast for 6-8 hours before serving.
